body:
I found that current rustc 1.13.0-nightly can't compile'Rust by Example - 8.2.5 As output parameters' code, both on my linux pc and [Rust Playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/).

I tried this code: see [Rust by Example 8.2.5](http://rustbyexample.com/fn/closures/output_parameters.html)

```
fn create_fn() -> Box<Fn()> {
    let text = "Fn".to_owned();

    Box::new(move || println!("This is a: {}", text))
}

fn create_fnmut() -> Box<FnMut()> {
    let text = "FnMut".to_owned();

    Box::new(move || println!("This is a: {}", text))
}

fn main() {
    let fn_plain = create_fn();
    let mut fn_mut = create_fnmut();

    fn_plain();
    fn_mut();
}
```

